codex
The graph build can produce artifacts that falsely claim the pinned corpus hash, and the sampler does not honor the requested sample size for the default run. These are correctness issues for the evaluation artifact.

Full review comments:

- [P2] Validate the corpus hash before stamping artifacts — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/python/eval/m1_graph_build.py:480-482
  When `--corpus` points at a stale or different JSONL, the script still emits the hard-coded `MUSIQUE_HASH`, so the coverage artifact can falsely claim it was built from the pre-registered Slice-4 corpus. Since this artifact is used as evidence for the M1 graph build, compute the file hash (or compare to the manifest) and fail before sampling when it does not match.

- [P3] Preserve the requested sample size — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/python/eval/m1_graph_build.py:124-126
  For proportional strata where the rounded per-hop allocations do not sum to `n`, this returns fewer or more questions than requested; with the checked-in MuSiQue answerable counts, `--n 300` produces 299 questions. That silently changes the evaluation sample size even though enough rows exist, so allocate the rounding remainder deterministically (or otherwise top up/trim) to make `len(out) == n` whenever `n < len(pool)`.
